gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Keeping skin hydrated isn't only about skincare. Some tips for dry skin are:&nbsp;</span><br></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">1. Avoid hot showers</span>: Hot water can further dry out your skin, so it's best to take lukewarm showers instead.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="background-color: var(--body_bg); color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">2. Humidify the air</span>: Dry air can worsen dry skin, so consider using a humidifier in your home or office to add moisture to the air.</span><br></p><p><span style="background-color: var(--body_bg); color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: inherit;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">3. Avoid over-washing:</span> Washing your skin too often can strip away its natural oils and make dryness worse. Try to limit washing your face to once or twice a day and use a gentle, non-foaming cleanser.</span><br></p><p><br></p><p>Hydrating dry skin may seem like a challenge, but with these recommendations and tips we hope your skin care journey can be a little easier. And remember finding the right routine takes time because It's all about discovering what works best for your skin.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>&nbsp;Let's get ready to enjoy the process of showing your skin you care, together!</p><p><br></p><p></p><p>